<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-676-254  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 676 254.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Sept 18 1989 v6 n37 p23(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Patient information system automates diagnosis process. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ANTRIM Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Anatomic Pathology System (Computer program) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     PatientsInformation SystemsHealth CareDiagnostic AssessmentInformation Storage and RetrievalProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Patient Information System Automates Diagnosis ProcessandM;PLANO, Texas -- What's a doctor to do when making a diagnosis with patientinformation that may be in different locations, scribbled in variousnotebooks or even inaccessibly situated in a word processing systemsomewhere?andM;Antrim last month introduced the Anatomic Pathology System, which allowsusers to archive, categorize and quickly retrieve patient diagnosticinformation for reporting and clinical studies, company officials said.andM;&quot;A pathologist doesn't have to act blindly; he can have information on pasthistory right at his fingertips when making a diagnosis,&quot; said Linda Martin,systems analyst at Antrim.andM;The product is a user-driven, real-time information system that enables usersto more speedily process specimens in a laboratory as well as provide patienttracking and historical analysis reporting, officials said.andM;Standard phrases and templates can be customized for each pathologist, andreport formats can be designed according to the requirements of a laboratoryor client.andP;  Patient results can be transcribed in batch mode or individuallyas dictation is finished.andM;In addition, the Anatomic Pathology System offers automatic Snomed codingusing the Snomed dictionary or Microglossary from the College of AmericanPathologiests.andM;Major features of the Anatomic Pathology System include management andstatistical reports; regional nomenclature cross-reference, text-editing andspell-checking capabilities; history search; correlation module; consultationmodule; follow-up module; and autopsy module, according to officials.andM;Diseases Can Be TrackedandM;&quot;Autopsies don't follow through the same order-entry and work-flow process,so we set up a complete module for that that meets the requirements of theAmerican College of Pathologiest,&quot; Martin said.andP;  &quot;We also include a familyflag feature that enables pathologiests to track diseases acrossfamilies--cancer, for instance, or diabetes,&quot; she added.andM;At present, the product runs on VAXes and PDP-11s, although the company willsoon add support for IBM PCs and, later, RISC Ultrix workstation, officialssaid.andP;  Prices for the system, which is available now, start at $20,000.andM;For additional product information, Antrim Corp. can be contacted at 101 E.andO;Park Blvd., Suite 1205, Plano, TX 75074, (214) 422-1022.andO;</TEXT></DOC>